WEBVTT

00:07.616 --> 00:12.708
♪♪

00:12.751 --> 00:15.624
Meredith: Our genes, which we
inherit from our parents,

00:15.667 --> 00:17.452
determine who we are
biologically.

00:19.106 --> 00:20.542
Just a heads-up --
the owner of the cabin

00:20.585 --> 00:22.413
has a very strict
no-phones policy,

00:22.457 --> 00:24.024
except in emergencies.

00:24.067 --> 00:25.634
I wouldn't want
to upset the owner.

00:25.677 --> 00:27.679
[ Chuckles ]
No, you wouldn't.[ Chuckles ] Right?

00:28.854 --> 00:30.204
Wow.

00:30.247 --> 00:32.206
It's more amazing
than you described.

00:32.249 --> 00:33.990
Well, the porch railing's
a little loose,

00:34.034 --> 00:35.296
and, you know, bears.

00:36.253 --> 00:37.646
But they're not inside,
so...

00:37.689 --> 00:39.474
Okay. Hmm.

00:39.517 --> 00:40.475
Our blueprint.

00:40.518 --> 00:42.520
♪♪

00:42.564 --> 00:45.219
Sorry, it's just
one last e-mail to Amelia

00:45.262 --> 00:46.742
about the FDA.

00:46.785 --> 00:48.787
And then you'll be done
changing the world?
Yes.

00:48.831 --> 00:50.093
[ Cellphone swishes ]Done.

00:50.137 --> 00:51.355
[ Chuckles ]

00:51.399 --> 00:52.356
Ready?
Yeah.

00:52.400 --> 00:53.488
Let's go.

00:55.098 --> 00:56.056
Man over PA:
Paging Dr. Hamilton

00:56.099 --> 00:57.405
to the Grey Center.

00:57.448 --> 00:59.407
Dr. Hamilton
to the Grey Center.

00:59.450 --> 01:02.497
Meredith: Everything from
our eye color to our height.

01:02.540 --> 01:04.629
Even our laugh.

01:04.673 --> 01:06.283
But, also, our diseases.

01:06.327 --> 01:07.937
Did I miss
the party invite?

01:07.980 --> 01:10.679
A very expensive
experiment succeeded,

01:10.722 --> 01:13.508
which means more money,
more people.

01:13.551 --> 01:15.249
More toys.
Is this a new 3D b--

01:15.292 --> 01:16.902
Don't.
I know.
Don't touch it.

01:16.946 --> 01:18.687
Did you see
Meredith's notes?

01:18.730 --> 01:20.515
She said we could
finish the report.

01:20.558 --> 01:23.083
Asthma, diabetes, cancers.

01:23.126 --> 01:24.388
And be done with all this?

01:28.349 --> 01:32.135
But who you are at your core
goes way beyond genes.

01:32.179 --> 01:35.312
98, 99, 100!

01:35.356 --> 01:38.141
Ready or not, here I come.So, the sun
is actually white?

01:38.185 --> 01:40.187
Yeah. Weird, huh?
Yeah.

01:40.230 --> 01:42.580
And it's not even
the biggest star.Is that true, Aunt Maggie?

01:43.320 --> 01:44.800
Huh?

01:44.843 --> 01:45.975
I'm so sorry.
What was it?

01:46.018 --> 01:47.890
What -- Ask me again.

01:47.933 --> 01:49.544
Well, I think you should
go lay down.

01:49.587 --> 01:50.545
No. No.

01:50.588 --> 01:51.763
I took the flu medication.

01:51.807 --> 01:52.808
I'm gonna rally,

01:52.851 --> 01:54.244
and I'm gonna help
with the kids.

01:54.288 --> 01:56.594
Well, you know I used to be
a camp counselor, right?

01:56.638 --> 02:00.337
I know CPR, and I've seen
every Marvel movie.

02:00.381 --> 02:03.210
And, you know,
the whole surgeon thing.

02:03.253 --> 02:05.299
It's just it requires
a different kind of training.

02:05.342 --> 02:06.604
I'll be fine.

02:06.648 --> 02:07.736
Let's just get you
upstairs and --

02:07.779 --> 02:09.172
I can't find Ellis.

02:10.086 --> 02:11.827
[ Sighs ]
Oh, God.

02:11.870 --> 02:13.611
Yeah, okay.
Here we go.

02:15.222 --> 02:16.527
Here we go.

02:20.314 --> 02:21.706
[ Chuckles ]

02:23.708 --> 02:26.581
You're rewriting your report
in your head, aren't you?

02:26.624 --> 02:31.238
I am still stuck on the part
where we explained

02:31.281 --> 02:33.979
why we chose to break up
the injection into four parts.

02:34.023 --> 02:35.546
Mm.

02:35.590 --> 02:36.591
When you work
on something like that,

02:36.634 --> 02:38.027
it invades your thoughts.

02:38.070 --> 02:40.160
It i-invades your dreams,
everything.

02:40.203 --> 02:41.161
It's weird.

02:41.204 --> 02:42.553
Two weeks ago,
I wrote out

02:42.597 --> 02:44.947
a cellular calculation
on Zola's homework.

02:44.990 --> 02:46.557
Well, think how smart
she looked.

02:46.601 --> 02:48.037
It was a history
assignment.
Oh.

02:48.080 --> 02:49.473
About 15 years ago,

02:49.517 --> 02:51.258
I got involved in a study
on liver transplants

02:51.301 --> 02:53.564
with HIV-positive donors
and recipients,

02:53.608 --> 02:54.826
and it was a lot
of ups and downs

02:54.870 --> 02:56.567
and flying
all over the country.

02:56.611 --> 02:58.352
And I wanted to be able
to turn my brain off

02:58.395 --> 03:01.659
every once in a while,
so...cabin.

03:01.703 --> 03:03.879
It was the first big purchase
I made just for me.

03:03.922 --> 03:05.272
Did it work,
to shut your brain off?

03:05.315 --> 03:06.447
The first few times
I came up here,

03:06.490 --> 03:08.275
I got a little stir crazy.

03:08.318 --> 03:10.146
Because there were
no lives to save.Not a single one.

03:10.190 --> 03:11.495
So, I had to settle
into the calm.

03:11.539 --> 03:13.541
[ Laughs ]

03:13.584 --> 03:15.107
Oh. What's that like?

03:15.151 --> 03:16.239
Takes some getting used to.

03:16.283 --> 03:17.893
[ Laughs ]

03:21.462 --> 03:23.812
You're not very good
at this, are you?
[ Laughs ]

03:23.855 --> 03:25.683
No. [ Sniffles ]

03:26.293 --> 03:27.729
♪♪

03:27.772 --> 03:30.340
Come here.
[ Chuckles ]

03:30.384 --> 03:31.733
[ Glass taps lightly ]

03:31.776 --> 03:41.743
♪♪

03:41.786 --> 03:46.965
♪♪

03:47.009 --> 03:48.619
I think we need to re-work
the way we tackle

03:48.663 --> 03:50.578
David's bowel obstruction.

03:50.621 --> 03:52.971
It reads like he was
intentionally trying to hide it.Didn't he?

03:53.015 --> 03:55.452
Maybe, but he's already been
accused of pay-to-play.

03:55.496 --> 03:57.062
Putting entire
responsibility on him

03:57.106 --> 03:58.325
would further
discredit him,

03:58.368 --> 03:59.674
just as he's looking
to widen the project.

03:59.717 --> 04:00.675
So we should
take the blame?

04:00.718 --> 04:02.111
I didn't say that, either.

04:02.154 --> 04:04.113
Hamilton's
primary care physician

04:04.156 --> 04:05.506
had examined
and cleared him,

04:05.549 --> 04:07.595
and he reported feeling fine
that morning.

04:07.638 --> 04:09.727
Patients with Parkinson's
are at risk

04:09.771 --> 04:11.512
for other
health conditions.

04:11.555 --> 04:13.078
Maybe we could have done more
on our end.

04:13.122 --> 04:15.037
Hamilton almost cost us
that entire surgery.

04:15.080 --> 04:16.430
Why would we lie?
We're not.

04:16.473 --> 04:19.128
But the goal is to further
Parkinson's research.

04:19.171 --> 04:20.390
Do you have to do that?

04:20.434 --> 04:21.870
Walk?
Pace.

04:23.872 --> 04:26.004
Fine, okay --
an argument could be made

04:26.048 --> 04:28.006
that due to the extreme
motivation of patients

04:28.050 --> 04:30.182
who are seeking
this experimental surgery,

04:30.226 --> 04:32.402
it requires more in-depth
history and physical pre-op.

04:32.446 --> 04:34.578
Right, okay.
Let's frame it like that.

04:34.622 --> 04:36.841
Thorough history-taking
and rigorous testing

04:36.885 --> 04:38.495
should be considered
before performing the surgery

04:38.539 --> 04:39.757
moving forward.

04:39.801 --> 04:40.584
Yeah, it doesn't
point fingers,

04:40.628 --> 04:42.325
and it focuses on outcomes.

04:42.369 --> 04:43.935
And it provides value
to future surgeries.

04:43.979 --> 04:44.849
Mm-hmm.

04:46.590 --> 04:48.200
Pacing works.

04:53.293 --> 04:54.990
[ Sighs ]

04:55.033 --> 04:56.470
So, are we ready
to submit this?

04:56.513 --> 04:58.472
I think we are.

04:58.515 --> 05:00.952
Okay, we are...

05:00.996 --> 05:01.779
done.

05:04.391 --> 05:05.957
We are.

05:06.001 --> 05:09.047
My flight doesn't leave
until tomorrow morning.

05:09.091 --> 05:12.007
Or I could change it...

05:12.050 --> 05:13.095
to today.

05:13.138 --> 05:14.139
Or you could stay.

05:14.183 --> 05:15.358
You wanna come to a show?

05:26.021 --> 05:28.545
[ Door opens ]

05:28.589 --> 05:30.025
What the --
Uncle Nick!

05:30.068 --> 05:31.722
Charlotte! What --
What are you doing here?

05:31.766 --> 05:34.725
Clearly,
we had the same idea.

05:36.640 --> 05:38.033
[ Chuckling ]
Can you give me a minute?

05:39.339 --> 05:40.557
Just a minute.

05:41.515 --> 05:43.168
♪♪

05:43.212 --> 05:45.083
[ Laughs ]

05:45.127 --> 05:46.346
Sorry.

05:46.389 --> 05:49.131
Ellis!
Ellis?

05:49.174 --> 05:50.741
[ Door closes ]Where is that girl?

05:50.785 --> 05:52.439
Well, she's not
in the bathroom.

05:52.482 --> 05:54.266
Ugh, God.
Are you okay?

05:54.310 --> 05:56.921
My sinuses have just turned
into a vise around my brain.

05:56.965 --> 05:58.401
[ Sighs ]

05:58.445 --> 06:00.838
Hey, doesn't she love
to hide in her closet?

06:00.882 --> 06:03.014
I checked.
She's not there.Ellis!

06:03.058 --> 06:05.234
How am I gonna tell Meredith
I lost one of her kids?

06:05.277 --> 06:07.062
We didn't lose her --
we just don't know where she is.

06:07.105 --> 06:08.063
Ellis!

06:08.106 --> 06:09.456
I can just hear
Meredith now.

06:09.499 --> 06:11.675
"I always knew
it was gonna be you."

06:11.719 --> 06:14.156
I found her!Oop.

06:14.199 --> 06:15.113
Mm. Mm.

06:16.724 --> 06:17.986
Here I come.

06:21.381 --> 06:22.556
Are you okay?

06:22.599 --> 06:23.905
Did I win?

06:23.948 --> 06:25.123
[ Laughs ]
Yeah, you sure did.

06:25.167 --> 06:27.082
Let's play again.No, let's not.

06:27.125 --> 06:30.128
Why don't you two go get
a juice box, all right?

06:30.172 --> 06:32.957
And I'll be right there
in a second.

06:33.001 --> 06:34.437
Ugh...
[ Sighs ]

06:34.481 --> 06:35.917
Hey, let me handle it.Mm.

06:35.960 --> 06:38.136
All right? You rest.

06:38.180 --> 06:40.138
Look how level-headed I was
during all that.

06:40.182 --> 06:41.139
[ Both laugh ]

06:41.183 --> 06:42.750
What is this?

06:45.361 --> 06:46.580
[ Sighs ]

06:49.800 --> 06:52.673
Oh, this looks like
some of Ellis' old stuff.

06:52.716 --> 06:55.502
I thought Meredith had all
of this stuff put in storage.

06:55.545 --> 06:57.155
Can I keep this?

06:57.199 --> 06:58.330
I don't see why not.

06:58.374 --> 07:00.115
I mean,
we can ask your mom.

07:00.158 --> 07:01.899
[ Gasps ] Wow.

07:03.161 --> 07:05.294
Wow.

07:05.337 --> 07:07.339
Is this for you,
Aunt Maggie?

07:07.383 --> 07:14.608
♪♪

07:14.651 --> 07:15.826
[ Breathes sharply ]

07:15.870 --> 07:20.918
♪♪

07:39.284 --> 07:41.896
Hi.
Charlotte:
Hey. [ Laughs ]

07:42.940 --> 07:44.986
Okay, let's try this again.

07:45.029 --> 07:46.509
Uh, Meredith,
this is my niece, Charlotte.

07:46.553 --> 07:49.033
Charlotte, this is
Dr. Meredith Grey.Hi, Charlotte.

07:49.077 --> 07:50.557
It's really nice
to meet you.

07:50.600 --> 07:51.949
He talks about you
all the time.

07:51.993 --> 07:53.908
Aww.
Wait, Dr.Grey?

07:53.951 --> 07:55.562
As in the -- the surgeon
that saved your kidney?

07:55.605 --> 07:57.520
Life.
But, yes, same one.

07:57.564 --> 07:59.217
You forgot to mention
that she's your girlfriend.

07:59.261 --> 08:00.915
Well, I wanted to properly
introduce you two.

08:00.958 --> 08:02.699
Well, that was definitely
an introduction.

08:02.743 --> 08:05.006
[ Chuckles ]
And, um, are you supposed

08:05.049 --> 08:06.181
to be dating your patients?

08:06.224 --> 08:08.139
He's not my patient anymore,
so it's fine.

08:08.183 --> 08:11.403
Who's this?Oh, uh, this is Silver.

08:11.447 --> 08:13.449
Silver? Okay.
Nice to meet you.

08:13.493 --> 08:14.929
You guys, uh, friends,
or...

08:14.972 --> 08:16.539
More like soul mates."Soul mates"?

08:16.583 --> 08:18.106
It's like we've known
each other lifetimes.

08:18.149 --> 08:19.194
Eras.

08:19.237 --> 08:21.501
♪♪

08:21.544 --> 08:22.850
Long time.

08:22.893 --> 08:24.025
Pretty far away from school.

08:24.068 --> 08:25.200
You know, mid-terms.

08:25.243 --> 08:26.854
I'm starving.

08:26.897 --> 08:28.551
I saw steak.I can eat.

08:28.595 --> 08:32.642
♪♪

08:32.686 --> 08:34.252
Let's eat.
Let's eat.

08:34.296 --> 08:36.994
♪♪

08:37.908 --> 08:39.431
Are you gonna open it?

08:39.475 --> 08:41.521
Well, it could be
for another Margaret.

08:46.656 --> 08:49.920
You know,
after my mom died...

08:49.964 --> 08:52.575
there was a fire
in my grandmother's house,

08:52.619 --> 08:54.446
and it burned up
a good part of it,

08:54.490 --> 08:56.579
including the bedroom
where my brother and I kept

08:56.623 --> 08:58.712
a lot of our stuff
in storage.

08:58.755 --> 09:01.192
I lost a lot
of pictures and books,

09:01.236 --> 09:03.325
and I lost
the last birthday card

09:03.368 --> 09:04.892
my mom had given me.

09:07.547 --> 09:08.722
I was devastated.

09:11.159 --> 09:14.728
And to this day,
I still dream about...

09:14.771 --> 09:16.643
seeing her handwriting again.

09:18.601 --> 09:20.168
You don't even
have to read it,

09:20.211 --> 09:21.778
but it's nice
that you have it.

09:21.822 --> 09:27.479
♪♪

09:27.523 --> 09:28.959
♪ When I think of you,
I don't know what to do ♪

09:29.003 --> 09:30.439
Do you want a soda?

09:30.482 --> 09:32.006
A water?

09:32.049 --> 09:34.791
I would love
a ginger ale.

09:34.835 --> 09:37.402
Can I get a ginger ale
and Coke, please?

09:37.446 --> 09:38.621
[ Chuckles ]

09:38.665 --> 09:40.797
I spent a lot of time
in places like this

09:40.841 --> 09:42.190
when I was younger.[ Chuckles ]

09:42.233 --> 09:43.887
What was that Amelia like?Lucky to have survived.

09:43.931 --> 09:45.280
High most of the time.

09:45.323 --> 09:48.022
Doing things she could not
remember the next day.

09:48.065 --> 09:50.633
Probably still brilliant.They call it high-functioning.

09:50.677 --> 09:53.680
Well, this Amelia
just helped a million patients

09:53.723 --> 09:56.160
get one step closer to a cure
for their horrible disease.

09:56.204 --> 09:57.422
♪ Shoot a hole into the sun

09:57.466 --> 09:58.641
To the one
who drilled the holes.

09:58.685 --> 10:01.644
To us.

10:01.688 --> 10:03.124
[ Indistinct chatter ]

10:03.167 --> 10:05.213
♪♪

10:05.256 --> 10:06.867
[ Food sizzling lightly ]

10:09.043 --> 10:10.653
Are you okay?
Yeah.

10:10.697 --> 10:12.220
Not exactly the night
I had planned,

10:12.263 --> 10:14.396
but I'm still gonna make you
the perfect steak.

10:14.439 --> 10:16.006
If Silver doesn't
eat it first.

10:16.050 --> 10:17.617
Yes, that is true.

10:17.660 --> 10:19.009
A little more cheese
would go a long way.

10:22.143 --> 10:23.927
So, Silver.Silver: Hmm?

10:23.971 --> 10:25.233
Cool name.Yeah.

10:25.276 --> 10:26.321
Real cool.It feels like who I am

10:26.364 --> 10:27.714
in this moment, you know?

10:27.757 --> 10:29.367
Bright, but overlooked.

10:30.630 --> 10:33.502
When I first met Silver,
his name was actually Oak,

10:33.545 --> 10:35.330
but he's much more
of a Silver now.

10:36.766 --> 10:38.681
I'm sorry -- [ Stammers ]
Silver's not your real name?

10:38.725 --> 10:39.900
Oh, it is -- for now.
Yeah.

10:39.943 --> 10:41.641
Uh, we're always
evolving, you know?

10:41.684 --> 10:43.643
So, I change my name
each time I feel

10:43.686 --> 10:46.123
like a different person.Huh.

10:46.167 --> 10:47.603
Is that often?No more than
the next person.

10:47.647 --> 10:48.778
[ Chuckles ]

10:48.822 --> 10:50.214
Mmm.

10:50.258 --> 10:51.476
Mmm, that's good.

10:51.520 --> 10:52.477
A little salty.

10:55.698 --> 10:56.873
Where did you two meet?

10:56.917 --> 10:58.570
In the woods.[ Chuckles ]

10:58.614 --> 11:00.921
Charlotte participated in one
of my micro-dosing experiences.

11:02.226 --> 11:03.793
Drugs?Psilocybin.

11:03.837 --> 11:05.316
So, 'shrooms?
Calm down.

11:05.360 --> 11:07.144
Real low doses.
You don't even feel it.

11:07.188 --> 11:08.624
As I understand it,
micro-dosing therapy

11:08.668 --> 11:10.060
is for people
with, uh, anxiety,

11:10.104 --> 11:11.888
depression,
substance abuse issues.

11:11.932 --> 11:13.542
Does that describe you,
Charlotte?

11:15.370 --> 11:17.415
We use it to get in touch
with our shadow selves --

11:17.459 --> 11:20.201
the parts of us that
we're ashamed and scared of.

11:20.244 --> 11:21.376
Not what it's for.
Meredith?

11:21.419 --> 11:24.292
Yeah?Uh, micro-dosing therapy --

11:24.335 --> 11:26.555
know anything about it?
I...

11:26.598 --> 11:29.384
have read some
of the science, sure.
Mm-hmm.

11:29.427 --> 11:33.214
I'm not sure I'm as educated
on it as Silver is.

11:34.432 --> 11:36.913
So, are you guys in some
of the same classes, or...?Nope.

11:36.957 --> 11:38.785
Uh, are we ready to eat?Silver: I'm not really
a college type of guy.

11:38.828 --> 11:40.743
I'm more of a student of life.
[ Chuckles ]

11:40.787 --> 11:42.702
So, as a student of life,
what do you do?

11:42.745 --> 11:44.181
We can learn a lot more
from traveling the world

11:44.225 --> 11:45.313
than sitting in a classroom.

11:46.793 --> 11:49.186
Okay, we're definitely
ready to eat.

11:49.230 --> 11:50.753
Mm. [ Sniffles ]

11:50.797 --> 11:52.189
We plan to really
study everything around us

11:52.233 --> 11:53.060
in Costa Rica.

11:54.670 --> 11:56.063
[ Clears throat ]Nick: I'm sorry.
"Costa Rica"?

11:56.106 --> 11:58.413
Are you guys planning a trip
after the semester's over?

11:58.456 --> 12:00.502
In two weeks.Is this some sort
of study abroad?

12:00.545 --> 12:03.766
Why pay tuition when you can
just go for a few months?

12:03.810 --> 12:06.203
I was gonna tell you.Tell me what?

12:07.639 --> 12:09.598
I'm leaving school.

12:09.641 --> 12:17.345
♪♪

12:17.388 --> 12:18.607
[ Birds chirping ]

12:18.650 --> 12:20.522
[ Sniffles ]

12:20.565 --> 12:26.441
♪♪

12:26.484 --> 12:28.008
[ Sighs ]

12:28.051 --> 12:37.800
♪♪

12:37.844 --> 12:39.584
Ellis: I have to admit
that letter writing

12:39.628 --> 12:42.805
is my preferred form
of communication.

12:42.849 --> 12:44.633
You're able to say
what you need to say

12:44.676 --> 12:47.549
without rude interruption
or interference.

12:48.855 --> 12:51.596
"There are things I should
probably say to you, Margaret,

12:51.640 --> 12:54.295
and there's no time
like the present.

12:54.338 --> 12:56.427
My recent diagnosis
has forced me

12:56.471 --> 12:59.387
to think about
my own mortality.

12:59.430 --> 13:00.605
The past."

13:01.389 --> 13:03.217
"And mistakes."

13:03.260 --> 13:05.088
♪♪

13:11.138 --> 13:13.793
"You know, I think I got
my desire to take care of people

13:13.836 --> 13:15.142
from my mother."I can't believe it's you.

13:15.185 --> 13:16.186
"She was the quintessential
housewife."

13:17.492 --> 13:19.233
"And everything,
down to the pleats

13:19.276 --> 13:22.845
in my A-line skirt,
had to be perfect.

