the occasional update

26:16.705 --> 26:18.228
about how you were doing."

26:18.272 --> 26:20.622
They did?"Of course, I declined."

26:20.666 --> 26:22.537
You declined?
Hmm.

26:22.581 --> 26:24.800
I'm not a dinner
invitation, Ellis.

26:24.844 --> 26:26.585
♪♪

26:26.628 --> 26:27.977
[ Breathes sharply ]

26:28.021 --> 26:29.457
You declined?

26:29.500 --> 26:31.851
You weren't the least bit
curious about me?

26:31.894 --> 26:33.287
You're the one who thinks
that everything you touch

26:33.330 --> 26:34.636
is extraordinary.

26:34.680 --> 26:36.203
Didn't want to see
if I fit the bill?

26:36.246 --> 26:38.466
No, no, no.
Look at me, Ellis.

26:38.509 --> 26:40.816
You don't get to
avoid me now.

26:40.860 --> 26:42.470
Look at me!What do you want me to say?!

26:42.513 --> 26:43.863
That I wish
it was different?

26:43.906 --> 26:46.648
That I wish that you
and Meredith and me and Richard

26:46.692 --> 26:48.824
could have been
one big, happy family?

26:48.868 --> 26:49.956
Well, that was
a childish fantasy.

26:49.999 --> 26:51.435
It was never gonna happen!

26:51.479 --> 26:53.046
I -- I'm here.

26:53.089 --> 26:56.353
Living every day in the shadow
of the great Ellis Grey.

26:56.397 --> 26:58.442
Her living and breathing
and walking and talking mistake,

26:58.486 --> 27:00.488
the one who wasn't
good enough to be approved.

27:00.531 --> 27:02.272
You don't know
how hard it was for me.

27:02.316 --> 27:04.840
But I picked up the pieces,
and I moved on.

27:04.884 --> 27:06.668
And I did it --
on my own.

27:06.712 --> 27:08.975
And I spent every day

27:09.018 --> 27:10.541
wondering why
I wasn't worthy.

27:10.585 --> 27:12.282
Didn't you ever think about
how I might feel?

27:12.326 --> 27:14.545
I made a decision,
and I stood by it.

27:14.589 --> 27:16.983
That decision not to see you
I do not regret one bit.

27:17.026 --> 27:19.550
That decision
I am proud of!

27:19.594 --> 27:21.509
[ Screams ]

27:21.552 --> 27:23.293
[ Breathing heavily ]

27:23.337 --> 27:24.947
♪♪

27:24.991 --> 27:26.645
[ Sighs ]

27:26.688 --> 27:28.516
[ Crying ]

27:28.559 --> 27:30.170
♪♪

27:30.213 --> 27:32.868
[ Running footsteps
approaching ]

27:32.912 --> 27:35.088
[ Door opens ]Baby, hey.

27:35.131 --> 27:36.089
What happened?
What's going on?

27:36.132 --> 27:37.046
Are you okay?[ Exhales sharply ]

27:37.090 --> 27:39.701
That woman --

27:39.745 --> 27:42.225
She's awful. She --

27:42.269 --> 27:43.792
[ Exhales sharply ]
She was exactly

27:43.836 --> 27:45.925
how Meredith
described her.

27:45.968 --> 27:47.666
I don't think I'm gonna
finish the letter.

27:48.971 --> 27:50.233
Then don't.

27:51.757 --> 27:54.150
And know that...

27:54.194 --> 27:56.718
whatever it says
does not change

27:56.762 --> 27:58.546
the amazing person
that you are.

28:01.201 --> 28:03.333
I know.
[ Inhales sharply ]

28:03.377 --> 28:04.552
Okay.

28:05.771 --> 28:07.729
I just wish I didn't
need her to know that.

28:07.773 --> 28:10.558
♪♪

28:10.601 --> 28:12.342
Come here.

28:12.386 --> 28:14.475
♪♪

28:20.568 --> 28:22.962
Finishing school is gonna
give you more options.

28:23.005 --> 28:24.441
It's something
most people do not have.

28:24.485 --> 28:26.008
Most people --
You're talking about Mom?
Yes.

28:26.052 --> 28:28.271
Your mom could have had options,
but she threw them all away.

28:28.315 --> 28:31.274
She made the same mistake
over and over and over again.

28:31.318 --> 28:32.667
I know. I was there.Then act like it!

28:32.711 --> 28:34.625
I'm not her!

28:34.669 --> 28:36.279
Oh, my --Wait, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
Please, stop.

28:36.323 --> 28:37.193
Stop, stop, stop,
stop, stop.
No, no.

28:37.237 --> 28:40.109
Stop, stop, stop.
I-I-I --

28:40.153 --> 28:42.721
Look, I just want
what's best for you, okay?

28:42.764 --> 28:44.244
Based on what youwant,
not what I want.

28:44.287 --> 28:46.115
No, based on a lot
of life experience.

28:46.159 --> 28:47.682
You know, most people
aren't like you.

28:47.726 --> 28:49.771
Not everyone wakes up one day
and immediately knows

28:49.815 --> 28:51.860
what they want to do.

28:51.904 --> 28:54.515
I need to figure
some stuff out by myself.

28:55.821 --> 28:57.779
Why can't that be okay?

28:58.780 --> 29:00.260
I just...

29:02.262 --> 29:05.439
I don't want you
to have to struggle.

29:05.482 --> 29:07.354
Will you give yourself
some more credit?

29:07.397 --> 29:09.835
Have you ever had
to bail me out of jail?

29:09.878 --> 29:12.272
Or, like, pick me up
off the side of the road?

29:12.315 --> 29:15.144
Or -- I don't know,
take pills out of my hand?

29:15.188 --> 29:16.972
No.
Because you did your job.

29:18.495 --> 29:21.150
I'm okay,
and it's because of you

29:21.194 --> 29:24.066
that I can even think
about traveling the world.

29:26.634 --> 29:30.116
I will go back to school.
I promise.

29:31.508 --> 29:33.032
Charlotte: I'll make sure
that I have options.

29:33.075 --> 29:34.555
But in order
for me to do that,

29:34.598 --> 29:38.820
you have to stop trying
to dictate my every move.

29:38.864 --> 29:41.040
You have to let me mess up

29:41.083 --> 29:43.477
and, like, change my mind
a few times.

29:43.520 --> 29:45.827
♪♪

29:45.871 --> 29:48.090
And if I do drugs...[ Scoffs ] Charlotte.

29:48.134 --> 29:51.615
...they will be
plant-based, okay?

29:51.659 --> 29:53.226
So calm down.

29:53.269 --> 29:54.836
[ Chuckles ]

29:54.880 --> 29:56.533
[ Sighs ]

29:56.577 --> 30:02.017
♪♪

30:02.061 --> 30:07.501
♪♪

30:07.544 --> 30:09.198
[ Insects chirping in distance ]

30:10.678 --> 30:13.028
[ Snoring softly ]

30:18.729 --> 30:27.651
♪♪

30:27.695 --> 30:29.218
Ellis:
"I do have one regret."

30:29.262 --> 30:30.872
[ Sighs ]

30:30.916 --> 30:32.439
Please, go.

30:32.482 --> 30:34.920
"I do wish that you
and Meredith could have met.

30:34.963 --> 30:37.444
She could have used a sister.

30:37.487 --> 30:38.924
She's so much like me.

30:38.967 --> 30:41.274
Stubborn, singular-focused.

30:41.317 --> 30:44.016
I have a feeling you would have
been a good influence on her."

30:44.059 --> 30:45.234
♪♪

30:45.278 --> 30:47.149
True sisters.

30:47.193 --> 30:49.456
♪♪

30:49.499 --> 30:50.936
We are.

30:52.807 --> 30:55.549
I wasn't the best mother
to Meredith.

30:55.592 --> 30:57.116
I had high expectations

30:57.159 --> 30:58.987
which she couldn't
always reach.

30:59.031 --> 31:01.903
♪♪

31:01.947 --> 31:04.950
But I did my best
with you,

31:04.993 --> 31:07.430
by giving you away.

31:07.474 --> 31:10.390
I knew you would be better off
with Bill and Diane.

31:10.433 --> 31:11.782
♪♪

31:11.826 --> 31:13.349
I was.

31:13.393 --> 31:21.401
♪♪

31:21.444 --> 31:29.539
♪♪

31:29.583 --> 31:33.630
♪♪

31:33.674 --> 31:36.546
Hey, my baby.

31:36.590 --> 31:38.157
[ Exhales sharply ][ Chuckles ]

31:38.200 --> 31:39.810
Mom!

31:39.854 --> 31:42.074
[ Breathes sharply ]

31:42.117 --> 31:44.163
[ Sighs ]

31:44.206 --> 31:45.425
Okay.

31:45.468 --> 31:48.907
[ Breathes deeply ]

31:48.950 --> 31:51.997
♪♪

31:52.040 --> 31:53.955
[ Breathes sharply ]

31:53.999 --> 31:55.130
♪♪

31:55.174 --> 31:57.219
[ Sniffles ]

31:57.263 --> 31:58.786
[ Exhales sharply ]

31:58.829 --> 32:03.225
♪♪

32:03.269 --> 32:05.662
[ Mellow tune plays on guitar ]

32:05.706 --> 32:08.535
♪♪

32:08.578 --> 32:10.929
Amelia: When did you get
into music?

32:10.972 --> 32:12.365
A few years ago.
Really?

32:12.408 --> 32:14.062
You looked like you'd been
playing since you were a kid.

32:14.106 --> 32:15.063
[ Chuckles ]

32:15.107 --> 32:17.326
It started
as a dare, actually.

32:17.370 --> 32:19.067
My friend took me
to an Open Mic Night,

32:19.111 --> 32:21.940
certain it would cure
my hatred of public speaking.

32:21.983 --> 32:23.419
Didn't work.
[ Chuckles ]

32:23.463 --> 32:24.725
[ Chuckling ] Clearly.

32:24.768 --> 32:27.380
No, still hate it,
but performing is different.

32:27.423 --> 32:29.860
It's like this deep
part of myself

32:29.904 --> 32:33.168
that doesn't get
to come out often...

32:33.212 --> 32:35.910
gets to be a rock star.

32:35.954 --> 32:37.825
You're real carefree
on stage.

32:37.868 --> 32:39.609
I am.

32:39.653 --> 32:41.176
And self-assured.

32:41.220 --> 32:43.265
♪♪

32:43.309 --> 32:45.964
Just when I feel like
I'm figuring my stuff out...

32:46.007 --> 32:48.314
[ Groans ]
...life lifes.

32:48.357 --> 32:50.620
Why do you pretend like
you're not a rock star yourself?

32:50.664 --> 32:53.101
♪♪

32:53.145 --> 32:55.495
Thank you
for flattering me.

32:55.538 --> 32:57.279
No, I-I'm wondering.

32:57.323 --> 32:59.412
Why do you self-deprecate?

32:59.455 --> 33:00.848
You're more than that.

33:00.891 --> 33:02.937
[ Siren wails in distance ]

33:06.158 --> 33:07.811
[ Chuckles ]

33:09.030 --> 33:10.727
I don't know.

33:10.771 --> 33:13.165
I guess...

33:13.208 --> 33:16.081
it's kind of become
my shield of armor.

33:16.124 --> 33:17.386
Protection.

33:17.430 --> 33:18.997
From what?

33:20.650 --> 33:22.609
From fully loving
every part of me.

33:24.132 --> 33:28.223
'Cause if I do, then...

33:28.267 --> 33:30.486
I deserve a love
that does the same.

33:30.530 --> 33:33.098
It took me a long time
to embrace all of who I am.

33:33.141 --> 33:36.536
So, outside love
is like icing.

33:36.579 --> 33:40.322
♪♪

33:40.366 --> 33:44.152
I don't even think
I know all of who I am.

33:44.196 --> 33:47.938
Well, I'm excited to get to know
all of who you are.

33:47.982 --> 33:52.378
♪♪

33:52.421 --> 33:53.857
Me, too.

33:53.901 --> 33:58.123
♪♪

33:58.166 --> 33:59.689
You sure you two
don't wanna come?

33:59.733 --> 34:01.604
Should be a sick
full moon ceremony.

34:01.648 --> 34:02.997
Meredith?
Sick full moon?

34:03.041 --> 34:04.390
I'm good.
We'll pass.

34:04.433 --> 34:05.739
It was nice meeting you.

34:05.782 --> 34:07.393
I'm glad my uncle has
someone else to worry about.

34:07.436 --> 34:09.438
Have a great time
in Costa Rica.

34:09.482 --> 34:10.265
We will.

34:11.658 --> 34:13.703
So, next weekend, yes?Yes, yes, yes.

34:13.747 --> 34:15.662
I will come, and I'll give you
all the deets about our trip.

34:15.705 --> 34:17.968
You know, coordinates, flights,
the trees I'll be touching.

34:18.012 --> 34:19.535
[ Chuckling ]
Okay. Goodbye.

34:23.061 --> 34:24.801
[ Sighs ]

34:30.242 --> 34:33.593
I'm sorry our weekend
got ruined.

34:33.636 --> 34:36.161
No, these are our lives.

34:36.204 --> 34:37.901
There's no need
to apologize for them.

34:38.859 --> 34:40.078
[ Exhales sharply ]

34:44.778 --> 34:46.519
I'm not used to help.

34:47.868 --> 34:49.087
Someone else's opinion.

34:49.130 --> 34:50.610
Well, if you know
anything about me,

34:50.653 --> 34:52.133
you'll have to
get used to it.

34:52.177 --> 34:53.352
Well, yeah,
that's not easy for me.

34:53.395 --> 34:54.701
I mean, how would you feel
if I was trying

34:54.744 --> 34:56.224
to give you help
when it comes to your sisters?

34:56.268 --> 34:57.704
I wouldn't like it,

34:57.747 --> 34:59.488
and I would tell you
you were wrong.

34:59.532 --> 35:01.621
Well, then, we'regonna
have to get used to it.

35:06.539 --> 35:08.802
Charlotte's a great girl.

35:08.845 --> 35:10.282
You did a really good job.

35:10.325 --> 35:11.587
The weird thing is,

35:11.631 --> 35:14.155
is I don't want her
to end up like me, either.

35:14.199 --> 35:16.288
So rigid one day,
she wakes up

35:16.331 --> 35:17.898
and wants to rethink
everything.

35:17.941 --> 35:19.682
Is that what you're doing?

35:19.726 --> 35:21.902
I chose a career where saving
one life means losing another,

35:21.945 --> 35:25.645
and every case feels harder
than the last.

35:25.688 --> 35:27.255
Are you thinking
about quitting?

35:27.299 --> 35:28.343
No.

35:28.387 --> 35:29.866
[ Chuckles ]

35:29.910 --> 35:30.998
I don't know.

35:31.781 --> 35:34.001
I don't -- I don't know.

35:37.918 --> 35:40.573
You know, Hamilton thinks that
I took the Parkinson's project

35:40.616 --> 35:43.358
because I'm really trying
to cure Alzheimer's.

35:43.402 --> 35:45.491
Is that true?
I don't know.

35:45.534 --> 35:47.232
But I also don't know
if I can just go back

35:47.275 --> 35:49.712
to Grey-Sloan and be
Chief of General anymore.

35:49.756 --> 35:51.497
[ Sighs lightly ]

35:51.540 --> 35:53.020
♪♪

36:00.027 --> 36:03.509
You know, I think today,
you saw that I'm not the, um --

36:03.552 --> 36:05.554
I'm not the most, uh...

36:05.598 --> 36:07.556
♪♪

36:07.600 --> 36:09.210
Patient?

36:09.254 --> 36:11.212
Yeah, that's it.

36:11.256 --> 36:14.215
Who is patient when it comes
to their family?

36:14.259 --> 36:16.609
♪ Think I got a new philosophy

36:16.652 --> 36:18.045
Not me.

36:18.088 --> 36:21.744
♪ I wanna dive right in

36:21.788 --> 36:23.572
I also have a temper.

36:23.616 --> 36:24.791
You have a temper?Yeah.

36:24.834 --> 36:27.010
Well, I don't believe it.[ Chuckles ]

36:27.054 --> 36:29.448
[ Chuckles ]

36:29.491 --> 36:30.840
♪ But I don't think
I know how to swim ♪

36:30.884 --> 36:34.366
I threw a retractor once.
Yeah.

36:34.409 --> 36:36.977
About eight years ago,
after losing a patient, I --

36:37.020 --> 36:38.631
♪ And when I'm standing
on the precipice ♪

36:38.674 --> 36:41.547
I didn't hit anymore,
but I-I think about it

36:41.590 --> 36:43.375
about once a day.

36:43.418 --> 36:46.639
I also have a very hard time
trusting people.

36:46.682 --> 36:48.771
And if you sell insurance
or you don't like dogs,

36:48.815 --> 36:50.033
you're dead to me.[ Chuckles ]

36:50.077 --> 36:52.253
Well, agreed on that.[ Chuckles ]

36:52.297 --> 36:54.516
♪ Some days I wonder
why I'm doing this ♪

36:54.560 --> 36:57.824
♪ So much easier
to love regret ♪I just --

36:57.867 --> 37:00.348
When I'm falling in love,
I-I-I --

37:00.392 --> 37:01.871
I mean, it scares me

37:01.915 --> 37:04.004
because I've done it
very rarely in my life.

37:04.047 --> 37:06.876
♪ My love, if I jumped in

37:06.920 --> 37:09.270
♪ Would you save me
from drowning? ♪I just don't love the feeling
of losing control.

37:09.314 --> 37:11.098
When you're falling
in love?

37:11.141 --> 37:12.578
♪ Is it too much to ask,
dear? ♪

37:12.621 --> 37:14.710
♪ I need to know Yeah, when
I'm falling in love.

37:14.754 --> 37:16.408
♪ I need to know
you'll be here ♪

37:16.451 --> 37:19.280
♪ My love, if I jumped in

37:19.324 --> 37:22.805
♪ Would you save me
from drowning? ♪

37:22.849 --> 37:25.591
♪ Is it too much to ask, dear?

37:25.634 --> 37:27.027
♪ I need to know

37:27.070 --> 37:30.639
♪ I need to know
you'll be here ♪

37:30.683 --> 37:34.295
♪ Stuck on the poolside

37:34.339 --> 37:37.124
♪ Trying just to get by

37:37.167 --> 37:42.085
♪ Been waiting a long time
just to know ♪

37:43.522 --> 37:47.917
♪ But the poolside's
all I know ♪

37:49.223 --> 37:51.181
Winston: There you go!Thank you.

37:51.225 --> 37:52.270
Is Aunt Maggie okay?

37:52.313 --> 37:54.272
Yeah.

37:54.315 --> 37:55.229
She's all right.

37:58.667 --> 38:00.103
Are you okay?

38:01.409 --> 38:04.369
Do you think my birth mother
thinks about me?

38:06.936 --> 38:08.242
Do you think about her?

38:08.286 --> 38:12.072
I wonder about her,
but I feel bad about it.

38:12.115 --> 38:14.335
I don't want to make
my mom sad.

38:14.379 --> 38:16.381
I think it's normal
to wonder where we came from

38:16.424 --> 38:17.860
and why we are
the way we are.

38:17.904 --> 38:19.471
And we can --

38:19.514 --> 38:21.560
we can have
different feelings about it.

38:21.603 --> 38:23.170
[ Mouths word ]

38:23.213 --> 38:24.476
Growing up, I didn't like
being around my dad

38:24.519 --> 38:26.956
because of some
of the decisions he made.

38:27.000 --> 38:29.611
But my mom --

38:29.655 --> 38:31.570
she was my hero.

38:31.613 --> 38:33.659
♪♪

38:33.702 --> 38:35.530
So's mine.

38:35.574 --> 38:38.881
♪ Your eyes look bored,
your brow's mean ♪

38:38.925 --> 38:42.276
♪♪

38:42.320 --> 38:46.672
♪ Looking upon
your lit up screen ♪

38:46.715 --> 38:48.891
♪♪

38:48.935 --> 38:52.330
♪ And the story
that plays out... ♪You know, you could stay.

38:52.373 --> 38:54.201
♪ ...is not clean [ Sighs ]

38:54.244 --> 38:55.768
I can't.
Why not?

38:55.811 --> 38:58.379
Because I'm a mom.

38:58.423 --> 39:01.861
♪ You can't un-see
what you've seen ♪And when I'm here
in Minnesota...

39:02.949 --> 39:04.516
[ Sighs ]

39:04.559 --> 39:07.040
...I miss my son
with every cell of my body.

39:07.083 --> 39:08.650
♪ I go walking out,
the storms upon me ♪

39:08.694 --> 39:10.609
And I hope that part of me
doesn't scare you away,

39:10.652 --> 39:14.961
because it is a part of me
that I truly, deeply love.

39:15.004 --> 39:16.963
♪ And I'm wandering about
upon the stone ♪

39:17.006 --> 39:18.834
♪♪

39:18.878 --> 39:24.405
♪ And the evening sky
is storming, too ♪

39:24.449 --> 39:26.364
♪♪

39:26.407 --> 39:29.802
♪ Was I better off

39:29.845 --> 39:31.978
♪ The less I knew?

39:32.021 --> 39:37.679
♪♪

39:37.723 --> 39:39.420
Meredith:
Who you really are

39:39.464 --> 39:41.422
is the result
of many, many things.

39:41.466 --> 39:44.294
♪ We're coming up in odd days

39:44.338 --> 39:45.992
How you deal with fear.

39:46.035 --> 39:50.562
♪ And one person's easy path's
another's maze ♪

39:50.605 --> 39:52.390
Who you surround yourself with.

39:52.433 --> 39:55.131
♪ And yet we go on unfazed

39:55.175 --> 39:56.872
I can't believe
she wrote this.

39:58.787 --> 40:00.920
It doesn't even
seem like her.

40:00.963 --> 40:02.443
[ Sighs ]

40:02.487 --> 40:03.792
It's not like
she mailed it.

40:03.836 --> 40:05.359
[ Lighter clicks ]

40:05.403 --> 40:07.579
She could have forgotten
she wrote it.

40:07.622 --> 40:09.755
♪ See the dog trees swaying Are you glad you read it?

40:09.798 --> 40:11.496
♪ Above the ground

40:11.539 --> 40:13.019
I don't know.

40:13.062 --> 40:14.977
I just...♪ And the cold

40:15.021 --> 40:17.240
...felt like I should.♪ Upon your skin

40:17.284 --> 40:19.460
♪ It feels so true

40:19.504 --> 40:21.984
I used to feel like
there was something missing,

40:22.028 --> 40:24.770
and I just figured
it was her.

40:24.813 --> 40:26.598
♪ Were you better off,
the less you knew? ♪

40:26.641 --> 40:29.383
♪♪

40:29.427 --> 40:30.993
I don't feel that way
anymore.

